ed. She was proved right within a decade of the book coming out.This reissue includes a new introduction by Benjamin Cohen of the University of California that contextualises the book, and conveys the value of the work for a modern audience.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEconomic historyx1945-. 0aEconomic historyy1945-. 0aInternational finance. 0aSpeculation. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh  aBank for International Settlements.  aCasino Capitalism.  aInternational Monetary Fund.  aUS-Japan axis.  afinancial crime.  aglobal financial system.  ainternational political economy.  amidlevel theory building.  apost-Cold War world.  atechnological change.  atransnational debt.1 aCohen, Benjamin J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStrange, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2015 eBook-Packagez978311128311140uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978178499724340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781784997243423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781784997243/original  a978-3-11-128311-1  Manchester University Press 2015 eBook-Packageb2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles